                  <persName id="t18310908-197-person1499">
                  SARAH 
                  SCHOFIELD
               <interp inst="t18310908-197-person1499" type="surname" value="SCHOFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-197-person1499" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-197-person1499" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Robert Schofield - he is a <rs id="t18310908-197-viclabel1022" type="occupation">salesman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-197-victim1498 t18310908-197-viclabel1022"></join>. On the 26th of July I went out, and on my return saw the prisoner at my street door; he asked about a black coat, which had laid in our window - I told him it was sold, and he went away; when I got into the shop I missed a waistcoat off the drawers, and another out of the drawers - he came next morning, between nine and ten o'clock, and asked if I had a white waistcoat to sell; I said No, and told him I had missed two waistcoats - he said if I called where he lived, at William-street, I should have his character - I went there with an officer, and found him; he denied the charge - I found the property at the pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-197-person1500">
